00.Summary:
Import SWIR in situ data (Section 2.1) of the full tensile test specimen. Arrays have been pre-processed as a dream3d file from the SWIR camera.


General alignment with the CAD target performed with Rotate Sample Reference Frame and Set Origin and Spacing.

04.Summary:
This section classifies anomalies within the micro-CT data using Otsu's method (Section 4.0).


Grayscale fillhole removes local minima

Attribute array calculator subtracts the density array from the fillhole array leaving only the local minima

Otsu Multiple Thresholds filter segregates the local minima into a seperate class

17.Summary: This section creates a mask of the part boundary and isolates the SWIR arrays of the part volume (Section 3.1).

24.Filter_Human_Label: Extract Internal Surfaces from Triangle Geometry

29.Summary:
This section performs registration using ICP to align the SWIR dataset to the CAD file (Section 3.1).


Iterative closest point computes a transformation matrix using the surface point clouds of both parts

Apply transformation to geometry peforms the transformation on the CT image array

32.Summary: The individual erors are measured from the surface point cloud in the SWIR dataset to the triangles in the CAD file using Vertex to Triangle Distances (Section 3.2).
